{
  "stem": "13469.5",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Or I remember-- I see on the plan, there's a bath house in Westerbork, so that's obviously where we reported, and where we had it.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We lived in three-tiered bunks.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they were metal constructed three-tier bunks.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And there were quite a lot of people living in the individual barracks.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I think it was reasonably crowded-- not as crowded as Belsen later on, but yes, they-- it was probably not all that good, the sleeping accommodation kind of thing.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But I think we had our meals together-- either in-- in either one of our barracks, or there were other dining halls, or something like that, where we perhaps had the meals together.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we had plenty of time to see each other, despite the fact that my parents worked and I worked.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And Rudy and Eve presumably hung around the camp all day, maybe they had some instructions here and there.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So I think we've covered most of my recollections from Westerbork.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] But it was then in January '44 when we, apparently, were told that we were going to be sent to another camp for-- where all the exchange people, kind of all the people with blue stamps from Westerbork.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And there was one transport in the middle of January-- we were not on that one.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But then then there was-- on the 1st of February was another transport.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "We could see, straight away, that it was different and better.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Because the train that came in was passenger coaches, not cattle trucks.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And-- and things like that mean an awful lot to you-- little things like that tend to immediately suggests various things.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And obviously, we could see that we were in a better situation than the people who had gone on the cattle trucks before.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
